snippet: A report of a possible miscount in one precinct during the Iowa caucuses has underscored the close race, and that anomalies are common during vote counting.
abstract: A report of a possible miscount in one precinct during the Iowa caucuses has underscored the close race, and that anomalies are common during vote counting.
lead_paragraph: 4:46 p.m. | Updated At just before 2 a.m. on Wednesday, Matt Strawn, the Iowa Republican Party chairman, addressed reporters who had spent the night following the historically close Republican caucus race between Mitt Romney and Rick Santorum. The margin separating the candidates was small -- eight votes -- but he was prepared to declare a victor. "Congratulations to Governor Mitt Romney, the winner of the 2012 Iowa caucuses," Mr. Strawn said.

headline.main: Iowan Casts Doubt on Winner of Caucus
